Class RingtonePickerDialog

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.support.v4.app.Fragment
      • android.support.v4.app.DialogFragment
        • com.kevalpatel.ringtonepicker.RingtonePickerDialog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.arch.lifecycle.LifecycleOwner, android.arch.lifecycle.ViewModelStoreOwner, ComponentCallbacks, DialogInterface.OnCancelListener, DialogInterface.OnDismissListener, View.OnCreateContextMenuListener 

    public final class RingtonePickerDialog
extends DialogFragment
    Created by Keval on 29-Mar-17. Ringtone picker dialog. Never initiate ringtone picker dialog directly using DialogFragment.show(FragmentManager, String). Use RingtonePickerDialog.Builder to initiate ringtone picker.
    See Also:
    RingtonePickerDialog.Builder

      • launchRingtonePicker

        private static void launchRingtonePicker(@NonNull
                                         FragmentManager fragmentManager,
                                         @Nullable
                                         String title,
                                         @NonNull
                                         String positiveButtonText,
                                         @Nullable
                                         String negativeButtonText,
                                         @NonNull
                                         ArrayList<Integer> ringtoneTypes,
                                         @Nullable
                                         String currentUri,
                                         @NonNull
                                         RingtonePickerListener listener,
                                         boolean isPlaySample)
        Create and display the RingtonePickerDialog.
        Parameters:
        fragmentManager - Support FragmentManager.
        title - Title of the dialog.
        positiveButtonText - Title for the positive button.
        negativeButtonText - Title for the negative button.
        ringtoneTypes - List of the RingtonePickerDialog.RingtoneTypes to display.
        currentUri - Current ringtone Uri.
        listener - RingtonePickerListener to get notify when new ringtone is selected.
        isPlaySample - True if the dialog should play sample ringtone else false.
